						<h2 style="font-weight: 850; letter-spacing: -0.02em;">Tiered <span class="text-gradient">Pricing</span></h2>
					</div>
					<p class="ec-services__subhead">Three tiers, priced by the complexity of your operation, channels, SKU count, locations, and how much of the function you hand us. Where you land depends on your store. Reach out and we'll place you in the right one.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="ec-pricing__grid">
					<div class="ec-pricing__card">
						<div class="ec-pricing__tier">Starter</div>
						<div class="ec-pricing__price"><span class="ec-pricing__amount">$5,000</span><span class="ec-pricing__period">/mo</span></div>
						<p class="ec-pricing__body">Single channel, straightforward catalog, one location. We centralize your data, run the core cadences and own the function end to end.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="ec-pricing__card ec-pricing__card--featured">
						<div class="ec-pricing__tier">Growth</div>
						<div class="ec-pricing__price"><span class="ec-pricing__amount">$7,000</span><span class="ec-pricing__period">/mo</span></div>
						<p class="ec-pricing__body">Multichannel or 1-5 locations, medium SKU count, decent SKU velocity. Full managed operations plus forecasting and tighter reconciliation across your 3PL and suppliers.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="ec-pricing__card">
						<div class="ec-pricing__tier">Scale</div>
						<div class="ec-pricing__price"><span class="ec-pricing__amount">$10,000</span><span class="ec-pricing__period">/mo</span></div>
						<p class="ec-pricing__body">Multiple channels, 5+ locations, high SKU count, high SKU velocity. The full function run on tight daily, weekly, and monthly cadences.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="ec-pricing__footer">
					<p class="ec-pricing__note">We'll scope your store on a short call and confirm the right tier.</p>
					<a href="/contact" class="ec-btn ec-btn--hero">
						<span>Let's Talk</span>
						<span class="ec-animated-dots">
							<span></span><span></span><span></span>
						</span>
					</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
		<!-- SECTION 6: FAQ                             -->
		<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
		<section class="ec-faq scroll-reveal">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="ec-faq__intro">
					<div class="section-header">
						<div class="badge">FAQ</div>
						<h2 style="font-weight: 850; letter-spacing: -0.02em;">Common <span class="text-gradient">Questions</span></h2>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="ec-faq__list">
					<details class="ec-faq__item">
						<summary class="ec-faq__q">We already have an operator. Why would we need you?</summary>
						<div class="ec-faq__a">We're not a replacement, we're leverage. We take the recurring, senior-heavy work off your operator's plate such as forecasting, variance investigation, PO reconciliation, reporting, so they focus on what needs a person in the building. You get more capacity without another hire.</div>
					</details>
					<details class="ec-faq__item">
						<summary class="ec-faq__q">We already use inventory software. Do we have to switch?</summary>
						<div class="ec-faq__a">No. We work with your existing tools, connect what isn't talking, and own the function on top of your stack. No migration, no rip-and-replace.</div>
					</details>
					<details class="ec-faq__item">
						<summary class="ec-faq__q">Why a retainer instead of project work or hourly?</summary>
						<div class="ec-faq__a">Because ops isn't a project, it's a function that runs every week. Inventory counts, PO reconciliation, variance investigation, and reporting don't stop, they happen on a daily, weekly, and monthly cadence. A retainer is how you keep a senior operator on that function continuously, not in one-off bursts.</div>
					</details>
					<details class="ec-faq__item">
						<summary class="ec-faq__q">Isn't it cheaper to just hire someone in-house?</summary>
						<div class="ec-faq__a">A full-time ops hire is slower to find, more expensive, and hard to scale back when things slow down. You also get one person's skill set. With us, you get a team that's already done this across multiple brands, for less than a senior salary, starting now.</div>
					</details>
					<details class="ec-faq__item">
						<summary class="ec-faq__q">How do you handle our data and supplier relationships?</summary>
						<div class="ec-faq__a">Everything runs under a signed agreement covering scope, IP ownership, and data security. We disclose the tools we use, including AI, and your data stays yours. We work inside your systems, not around them.</div>
					</details>
					<details class="ec-faq__item">
						<summary class="ec-faq__q">What if we want to bring it in-house later?</summary>
						<div class="ec-faq__a">That's fine. We build clean systems and documented workflows, so if you ever staff up internally, you're inheriting an organized function, not a black box. Most clients expand scope with us instead&mdash;but the door's never locked.</div>
					</details>
					<details class="ec-faq__item">
						<summary class="ec-faq__q">What size brand is this for?</summary>
						<div class="ec-faq__a">Built for growing Shopify brands roughly in the $1M&ndash;$10M range&mdash;big enough that ops is breaking spreadsheets and a founder's memory, not yet big enough to justify a full in-house ops team.</div>
					</details>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

